one_reviews_text: Great App
The idea is good, but I think it could be more fun, and shorter... It's time waisting in 50%
Personally not into electronic, but I still enjoyed it. So if you are, by all means...
Would love to see it available for the quest

review_title: A neat music video in VR
one_reviews_text: Nothing really crazy, but some blocks progressing to the music. I could see something like this expanding into a full album if you just wanted to watch visuals inspired by music. It’s worth checking out, as it is free, if you want to see more than the store trailer in actual 3D.

Well, I loved it.  There's a real sense of presence with this.  It's a strange land where you experience some sort of intelligence.  Good music.  I'd like to know if the maker has done anything similar since. Good music that needs to be loud and abrasive (because that fits the atmosphere that is being transmitted).
review_feedback:
We did some other games (KIN for example) and some other smaller games, but those are not available as they where for Muse's latest world tour VIP lounge.
Arjan also has some other music available on his own site : www.arjanm.com

one_reviews_text: Very cool visuals

I swear I did not get the same app everyone else did. I first tried this with my Rift headphones all the way up. It was as painful as the shrill shrieks in A Large Quantity of Mushrooms. OK, my bad for having my volume up, So I retried it with the volume almost off. Bearable, but the bright mushroom cloud was actually painful to look at. I’m happy people liked it, but if you are sensitive to certain noises or bright lights this will drop you like a stun gun.
Pretty interesting VR music experience. I really like that there was a semblance of progression, not just random visuals. The physics-based movement is pretty interesting.

review_title: People seem to like anything, not good..
one_reviews_text: Well this is just a very basic music video, as far as music videos go its ok, nothing special, and the music is more like constant sound effects rather than a song and I personally dont think as a song it was very good at all and I am someone with a huge stereo system (5x 15 inch subs, 2x 12inch & 2x 10 inch plus the Speakers all in one room!) and I have some of the best Headphones money can buy and am a big music lover, this is a very short video clip and isnt very interesting, personally I would skip it, not worth the time, Check out "Lost" the short video which is 10 times better!
Not as good as Fantasynth but still an enjoyable experience.

review_title: A great start and a fun demo
one_reviews_text: There are some really cool concepts in here. Some of it just kinda rolls blankly but the music is really good. There are a few "oh wow!" moments. I would love to see what this author could do if they had more time and money. I look forward to their next one!
Nice music and animation. Before the final part there are a few seconds of boring nothingness. But overall it was great. Thank you for this!! Going to show it to my friends and family.
It was ok
Only got interesting at the very end with the giant walking dudes, but that part was too short.

Being able to feel the music is something VR does well and in this musical VR experience video you will discover how good it can be. The music might not be to your own tastes, but it is still worth watching it anyway just to experience it. Is this the future of music videos? Maybe it is, but when will future musical experiences like this start costing us money to experience? My guess it will be sooner rather than later. But for now this one is free and well worth a download.
This was the first audio/visual app of this kind that I tried, about a year ago.  It's just the right length, good tune, fairly simple but very effective visuals.  Great job.
Good music, cool visuals.  It felt like I was inside of an abstract music video.  Loved it.
This was one of my first Experiences for the Rift. Nice to see it made it to the official store. Evereyone should have seen this! It's relly great! Also a good show-off for VR-Newbies.
Pretty nice and beautiful introducing demo. Recommended.
i want my 5 minutes back!
I don't even know what to call this, but it's great to just watch.  If you like electronic music, you'll likely enjoy this very much
generic but ok
Love the way the visual build with the music and the ending is breath taking.
First tried this on the DK2 a while ago. Mouth left open for the majority of the experience. Brief, awe inspiring experience. Well worth the price ;) 8/10

review_title: A VR Music Video Done Right
one_reviews_text: One of my favorite passive VR experiences. There is a great feeling of progression into the 3D space throughout this piece. Both visuals and music were well thought out and executed.
It was a beautiful experience. Now i want more of it. I just loved this. The music and the scenes were awesome.
A very well-developed conceptual experience. You can not rate it badly. It's really beautiful.
We need more VR demo scene stuff like this! Great experience.
that's about it... music was generic and it was fun to see something non 360-video for a change.

I liked the music, and amazing concept for VR music videos. Wish more people would make music video experiences of this qualtiy!

If there were one downside though it's that you can only watch it so many times, and there isn't much reason to come back after that.
Pretty cool
This was a beautiful experience
Music experience.  Short, but nice.

This was very fun to watch. 

Only issue I had was dealing with the sun rays in the one scene.
nice
